            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-420] Provide a non-pooling connection manager</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-420</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>The current implementations of the connection managers all have a connection&lt;br/&gt;
pool. For applications requiring only single requests very rarely this is&lt;br/&gt;
overkill. We should provide a very simple connection manager that uses a&lt;br/&gt;
connection only one time and then closes it right away.</description>
